Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities of Three Binary Monoglyme + 1-Alcohol Systems from (283.15 to 313.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The densities and viscosities of the binary mixtures of ethylene glycol dimethyl ether (monoglyme) with ethanol, 1-pentanol and 1-octanol were measured for the whole composition range at (283.15, 293.15, 303.15, and 313.15) K and normal atmospheric pressure. The excess molar volumes have also been obtained for each of the systems and temperatures. The kinematic viscosity data were fitted using a four-body McAllister equation.
